Ten-fold dilutions of BVDV-1 standard RNA were used to construct a standard curve that spanned nine orders of magnitude, from 101 to 109 copies of standard RNA, and showed linearity over the entire quantitation range, providing an accurate measurement over a very large variety of starting target amounts. The coefficient of linear regression (R
2) was equal to 0.998 and the PCR efficiency ranged around 99%, with a slope of −3.682 (Fig. 2
).
